sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total of 28,641 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 2.9 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 65.2% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month of 4.4 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $200 strike call option expiring October 05, 2018 , with 1,825 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 182,500 underlying shares of HD.

Lilly (Eli) & Co (Symbol: LLY) saw options trading volume of 23,037 contracts, representing approximately 2.3 million underlying shares or approximately 62.5% of LLY's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.7 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $110 strike call option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 1,477 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 147,700 underlying shares of LLY.

And Adobe Systems Inc (Symbol: ADBE) saw options trading volume of 19,505 contracts, representing approximately 2.0 million underlying shares or approximately 61.2% of ADBE's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $265 strike call option expiring October 05, 2018 , with 838 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 83,800 underlying shares of ADBE.
